                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12725306" author="drwoods" created="Mon, 29 Jun 2009 19:30:14 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;patch that cleans up the jvm arguments&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12740655" author="drwoods" created="Fri, 7 Aug 2009 18:56:41 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Removing the test.jvm.arguments in openjpa-slice and validation fixed the problems for me on Linux.&lt;br/&gt;
Note:  You will need to supply MAVEN_OPTS for your 64bit Java 6 builds, like the following (which resolved the automated build failures we were seeing):&lt;br/&gt;
   MacOSX and Windows - MAVEN_OPTS=&quot;-Xmx1024m -XX:MaxPermSize=256m&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
   Linux - MAVEN_OPTS=&quot;-Xmx1024m -XX:MaxPermSize=512m&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
